com.iha.emulator.control.task

Class ValueParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iha.emulator.control.task.ValueParameters

  • public class ValueParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    Information about values, that are enabled. Used in "Performance Simulation". When creating SimulationTask random values are created. Each simulation task can have own enabled values.
    Author:
    Filip Sutovsky

      • getEnabledValue

        public Value getEnabledValue(int valueIndex)
        Returns new instance of value, if given value index is in enabled values list.
        Parameters:
        valueIndex - index of value, that is to be created. This index is number of value in Value.Type
        Returns:
        new instance of value or null if given value index is not enabled.

      • copyDeepFoundValue

        private Value copyDeepFoundValue(Value foundValue)
        Creates new instance of same type as value given as parameter. New value will have same value,initial value and name as given value. Store history and generate value flags are automatically set to false.
        Parameters:
        foundValue - value to be copied
        Returns:
        deep copy of given value

      • saveToXml

        public org.dom4j.Element saveToXml(org.dom4j.Element rootElement)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
